verbose_text: In another trial, Palacios et al. XREF_BIBR reported that Puerto Rican obese men and women who consumed four servings of low-fat milk, cheese, and yogurt daily for 21 weeks had no differences in total body bone mineral content or density from baseline or compared with those who consumed 1,200 -1,300 mg of calcium per day from a dietary supplement or those who consumed less-than-recommended amounts of dairy foods and no calcium supplement (< 700 mg calcium / day).
evidence: amounts of dairy foods and no calcium
